narratives.question_text: Comments.If you wrote a paper with any of these professors, if the course was taught by more than one professor, or you would like to comment on any aspects previously mentioned
comments: I felt that this Clinic could have been better managed. The training sessions were too much of an information dump, that still left us a bit in the deep end of the pool for dealing with our clients. This led to lots of back and forth on documents, which felt like a very inefficient process. I thought the class sessions could have covered more law on non-profits, or included more class discussion.
The clinical faculty are great! Their lectures can sometimes be a bit dry but their advice about transactional lawyering and their responsiveness to individual student questions is fantastic.
